# Project Context
This is a Next.js 15 blog/portfolio site using TypeScript and Tailwind CSS.
The site is deployed on Vercel and serves as a personal frontend lab for experiments and blog posts.

# Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow Next.js 13+ App Router conventions
- Use Tailwind for styling (avoid custom CSS unless necessary)
- Prefer server components unless client interactivity is needed
- Use semantic HTML and accessible components
- Follow React best practices and hooks guidelines

# File Organization
- Blog posts go in /content/blog/ as markdown files with frontmatter
- React components go in /src/components/
- Utilities and helpers go in /src/lib/
- Use the app directory for routing (app router)
- Keep static assets in /public/

# Content Guidelines
- Blog posts should have proper frontmatter (title, date, excerpt, tags, published)
- Use descriptive file names with kebab-case for blog posts
- Include alt text for images
- Write engaging, personal content
- Maintain consistent tone and style

# Dependencies
- Prefer using existing dependencies over adding new ones
- Use yarn as package manager (never npm)
- Keep bundle size in mind
- Check for security vulnerabilities regularly

# AI Assistance Preferences
- Explain architectural decisions in comments
- Include comprehensive error handling
- Suggest performance optimizations when relevant
- Maintain consistency with existing code patterns
- Focus on accessibility and SEO best practices
- Provide TypeScript types for all functions and components
- Consider mobile-first responsive design

# Development Workflow
- Always test changes locally with `yarn dev`
- Use meaningful commit messages
- Deploy happens automatically via Vercel on push to main
- Check for linting errors before committing
- Follow the guidelines in START_HERE.md for adding content

# Security & Performance
- Sanitize any user inputs
- Optimize images and assets
- Use Next.js built-in optimizations
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Follow SEO best practices
